WSP Canada Inc.


Thornhill, ON

Canadian Pacific is a transcontinental railway in Canada and the United States with direct links to major ports on the west and east coasts. CP provides North American customers a competitive rail service with access to key markets in every corner of the globe. CP is growing with its customers, offering a suite of freight transportation services, logistics solutions and supply chain expertise. Visit cpr.ca to see the rail advantages of CP. For more on our purpose, culture, and strategy, visit cpr.ca/en/about-cp.

POSITION DESCRIPTION:
As the Assistant Trainmaster you will assist in the efficient movement of traffic within the road territory and yard-terminal by developing, organizing and executing the daily yard-terminal/road operating plan in a safe and cost effective manner which maximizes fluidity and achieves Local Service Operating Plan (LOSP) and Operating Plan (OP) compliance on a daily basis. This includes all processes related to arrival, classification, building, inspecting and dispatching of trains. You will also provide leadership accountability for inputs and outputs of safety, service, productivity and financial metrics.

POSITION ACCOUNTABILITIES:
Direct yard processes to fulfill customer car orders, Customer Service Operations instructions and Mechanical and Engineering requests for car movement and placement;
Accountable for delivering instructions for train movements within terminal to Dispatching and Operating crews;
Assist in the coordination of all train movements within the yard and on the mainline;
Accountable for asset utilization within the terminal
Accountable for expedited train movement to reduce and meet terminal dwell time
Update times, delays and variances in NEXUS/Yard Planner on a continuous basis (as required)
Validate mechanical requirements are met for car repair spotting and inspection to maximize track availability
Communicate with employees for all safety initiatives and blitz’s required in the terminal
Ensure all documentation is accurate, complete and properly communicated to the next Assistant Trainmaster on shift;
Resolve non-compliance crew issues and/or opportunities for process improvement, or escalate to the Trainmaster as appropriate;
Trouble shoot daily problems and concerns and resolve by implementing action plans and standard process
Perform efficiency tests and other safety activities to meet required standards;
Review workload for LSOP assignments to ensure maximum production and efficiency of assignments;
Contribute to the overall execution of the LSOP and OP through active supervision;
Accountable for inventory management of terminals and line of road in their areas of responsibility;
Assist in crew transportation to and from trains, away from home terminal hotels and for over the road requirements
Accountable for Transfer of Liability (TOL) notification (as required);
Accountable for notification and escalation of customer delays;
Responsible for job / safety briefings of the crews;
May be assigned Train & Engine employees to mentor and coach through active observation and providing feedback.

POSITION REQUIREMENTS:
Must possess a High School diploma or GED;
Previous operations related experience would be considered an asset;
Must be able to understand the Operating Plan & Local Service Operating Plan and compliance to it as it pertains to the yard;
Qualified Locomotive Engineer is an asset;
Must become Conductor or Engineer qualified and occasionally operate trains;
Must be or become rules qualified (CROR - Canadian Rail Operating Rules);
Must maintain certifications and licenses (i.e. Engineer Certification);
Must have a valid driver's license;
Must have strong computer skills;
Must be detailed orientated;
Must have strong attention to detail skills;
Ability to understand and work with collective agreements and other applicable regulations;
Ability to drill down, understand root cause and resolve complex issues;
Willing to be available as required on a 7x24 basis.

WHAT CP HAS TO OFFER:
Flexible and competitive benefits package
Competitive company pension plan
Employee Share Purchase Plan
Performance Incentive Program
Annual Fitness Subsidy

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION:
As an employer with national presence, the possibility does exist that the location of your position may be changed based on organizational requirements.

Medical Requirements:
Operating safely is a core foundation of CP. Our commitment is to protect our people, customers, communities in which we operate, the environment and our assets. We are also committed to a healthy and safe workplace. CP’s Alcohol and Drug Policy and Procedures (“Policy and Procedures”) support these commitments. All new hires for a safety critical position will be required to complete a pre-employment medical that includes a physical, vision, hearing, alcohol and drug audit assessment. Pre-employment qualification drug test(s) are also required. This includes candidates participating in the Trainee Program who will also be required to pass a drug test during the training process before receiving final qualification for the position.

Management Conductor Program:
Becoming a qualified conductor or locomotive engineer is the single best way for a management employee to learn the business at CP. You may be required to obtain a certification or to maintain your current certification/qualification as a conductor or locomotive engineer.

CP is an equal opportunity employer committed to the principles of employment equity and inclusion. We welcome applications from all qualified individuals. All applicant information will be managed in accordance with the federal Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act ("PIPEDA").

Overview
PKM Canada Marine Terminal LP (Vancouver Wharves Terminal) is currently recruiting for an Electrical Project Manager to join the team. This position reports to the Manager, Operations Engineering in the Natural Gas Liquids Business Unit (NBU), part of Pembina’s Facilities Division. Located in one of the busiest port cities in North America, our Vancouver Wharves’ location is one of the largest terminals on the West Coast and handles both liquids and bulk products including mineral concentrates, diesel, Sulphur, and grain products on behalf of customers.
The Electrical Engineer is responsible for the overall plant electrical infrastructure and the physical layer of the control system. This position will manage capital improvement projects and oversee the project definition, planning, execution and close out. As well, this role will act as a technical resource for the development and delivery of plant initiatives and electrical standards. The role works closely with Managers, SSEM staff, Operations Coordinators, Operations Logistics Analysts, 3rd party stakeholders, ILWU Foremen, and ILWU Longshore personnel to develop functional solutions and to provide electrical governance that promote safe, efficient, and environmentally responsible terminal services to our customers.
Summary of Responsibilities
This position manages capital projects related to the electrical and control infrastructure in the Vancouver Wharves plant. They are responsible for reviewing the current state and create long term improvement plans to optimize the capacity and lifespan of the plant’s electrical equipment. The position will work with the engineering manager to champion the improvement plan and allocate capital funds to the initiative This position will also provide ongoing technical support to operations and maintenance department for the electrical infrastructure.
Responsibilities will include but are not limited to:
Providing experienced and skilled design and management of projects from proposal stage through conceptual design, detailed design, construction, and completion stages;
Coordinating technical staff and consultants participating on projects;
Coordinating the preparation of documents required for approvals, preparing development and construction cost estimates and tender documents and contracts;
Demonstrating a commitment to the improvement, and adherence of safety and environmental policies in all work environment areas and promoting a positive safety culture through leadership by example; and
Contributing to a team environment that values inclusion & diversity.
Qualifications
Must be registered or eligible for registration as a professional engineer (P.Eng.);
Electrical engineering degree or electrical/electronic engineering technology diploma or Red Seal trade;
Medium to high voltage experience;
Detailed understanding of CSA standards and practice around electrical safety and maintenance;
Electrical FSR: Class A - Certification preferred;
Hands on experience power distribution design, motor control, fiber optics, ethernet and industrial communications instrumentation, PLC and HMI based control solutions;
Previous experience managing projects in an industrial environment;
Previous industrial labour relations experience an asset;
Solid computer skills, with experience with AutoCAD, CMMS Systems and MS Office suite; and
Strong attention to detail.
Additional Information
This position is considered “Safety Sensitive” so will require Pre-Employment Drug & Alcohol Testing. You may also be required to provide a Driver’s Abstract.
The successful candidate must live within 100 km of North Vancouver.
Qualified candidates are invited to submit their resume and covering letter by clicking on the following link prior to the position closing at midnight on Tuesday January 18, 2022.
careers.pembina.com/job/North-Vancouver-Electrical-Engineer-BC/814283000/
You can also access our careers at www.pembina.com

Propak Systems Ltd. is an established leader in engineering, fabrication, and construction of gas compression and processing facilities for the energy industry. Propak offers a competitive compensation and benefits package. We are currently seeking a Document Control Expeditor (Records Maintenance) for our Airdrie, AB office.
The Document Control Expeditor (Records Maintenance) is responsible for the records and data management needs of the Engineering and Drafting Department. The position possesses detailed knowledge of the department's operations. Duties include expediting documentation and liaising with vendors.
Key Responsibilities:
Maintains incoming vendor documentation;
Runs reports for material document part numbers for desired received dates;
Confers with vendors about delivery status of documentation as per Purchase Orders;
Liaises with Project Document Controllers, Project Engineers, Vendors, and Accounts Payable;
Provides data base entry and maintenance of Visual Manufacturing system;
Provides support to Document Control in relation to documentation required for Data Books and Operating Manuals;
Provides administrative support to Engineers as required;
Provides backup for Engineering Document Control;
Conducts electronic quality checks;
Assists with general software duties.
Qualifications:
2+ years’ experience as an Expeditor for the oil & gas industry or in a manufacturing and/or fabrication environment
2+ years’ office administration experience
Working knowledge in Visual Manufacturing or similar ERP system is an asset
Proficiency with the Microsoft Office suite of programs
Propak Systems Ltd. thanks all applicants for their interest however only those selected for an interview will be contacted.
No Phone Calls Please
Experience
Required
2 year(s): Office Administration
2 year(s): Expeditor experience within oil & gas industry

Company Overview
Teledyne DALSA is a global leader in the design and production of image sensors, cameras and acquisition equipment for various applications such as industrial automation, medical imaging and scientific observation. We develop best-in-class products with a talented team of people engaged with creating leading edge imaging technology.
Position Summary and Responsibilities

We are currently seeking a Technical Leader for our InGaAs initiative.
In this position you will lead development teams from product ideation through to production. The role requires a proven ability to lead multi-disciplinary teams in the development of highly technical products. You will work with the project manager and the project team members to deliver technical solutions and products that demonstrate technical compliance and provide high quality, reliability, manufacturability and usability while meeting the project schedule, budget and the risk tolerance profile.
As the Technical Leader for one or more project teams consisting of scientists, engineers, technologies and/or technicians, originality and good judgement are required in planning and developing new methods or techniques.
Execute critical image sensor development programs by planning, resourcing, and coordinating multi-disciplinary global teams – programs are multi-year and span from product ideation through to new product introduction
Supervise the activities of the project team members and conduct project related performance reviews for project team members;
Ensure chosen technical approaches are consistent with the project needs and scope and future technology roadmap, and perform risk assessment and execute on risk mitigation plan;
Work closely with the project manager to create and maintain project plans by adhering to component and tooling cost guidelines;
Develop and manage the supply chain
Continuous communication with customers to understand their needs and translate these needs into product features and specifications, while assisting in the preparation of custom product bid and proposals;
Participate in all aspects of project implementation including conceptualization, architectural analysis, detailed design, modelling, simulation, analysis, prototyping, component procurement, build, test and documentation and prepare procurement specifications for components, equipment and services;
Ensure adherence to and implementation of required Assembly, Integration and Test (AIT), Product Assurance (PA), and Quality Assurance (QA) plans;
Supervise activities required to prepare the product for manufacturing hand-off/NPI;
Prepare a complete set of project documentation, including milestone documents, build and test procedures, manufacturing specifications, user manuals, datasheets, application notes or other required user documents;
Thoroughly review and verify the technical content of all documents, drawings, models and files before releasing in the document control systems and before supplying to the customers and vendors/subcontractors;
Establish technical direction for new product development and review new product designs for feasibility of manufacture, including analysis of tolerances and specifications as they relate to performance of Teledyne Dalsa products;
Identify sources of technologies and assess applicability to Teledyne Dalsa as well as future development inter-dependencies, evaluate and recommend tools, services and equipment.
Qualifications
Bachelor, Master or Phd Engineering Degree in Electrical, Computer , Mechanical Engineering, Engineering Physics or Physics;
10+ years of experience in a role with responsibility for the design and development of electronic products or equivalent;
Knowledge of rapid product development strategies and process deliverables;
Strong project administration and planning skills with attention to detail;
Solid abstract thinking and problem solving skills

